def: One who, or that which, modulates. Denham.
The solid or insoluble portion of the cell protoplasm. SeeHygroplasm.
In an organic manner; by means of organs or with reference toorganic functions; hence, fundamentally. Gladstone.
A division of Crinoidea including numerous fossil species inwhich the body is covered with tessellated plates.
The mercury and foil on the back of a looking-glass.
Anything used in fitting up; especially (pl.),
A heavy wind; a wind that brings a storm; the blast of a storm.Longfellow.
In a straddling position; astride; bestriding; as, to sitastraddle a horse.
Having the ganglia of the nervous system unsymmetricallyarranged; -- said of certain invertebrate animals.
